<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1214> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1214" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Censorin. DN 17.10; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc., omits Lentulus; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.18; cf. CIL 1\n     .2.18, on Cornelius; see Degrassi 44f., 117, 438f. Both Consuls campaigned agains the Boii and other Gallic tribes, then Varus transferred his operations to Corsica while Caudinus fought the Ligurians (Zon. 8.18; cf. Polyb. 2.21.5-6; Liv. Per. 20), and celebrated a triumph over them (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 549; Eutrop. 3.2 with praenomen L.)." .
